ss with authorization2star  aCommemorating John Moorman's immense contribution to Franciscan history across five decades, the essays in this collection reflect upon Moorman's diverse writings on biography, hagiography, history, art, and prosopography. Contributors draw upon Moorman's diaries and his materials for a biographical register of the Franciscans in medieval England. The volume is in tune with recent developments in Franciscan history in general, with a special interest in the English province. This is exemplified by studies on Franciscan iconography; the English province's impact of the wider order; the scholastic enterprise; prosopography; economy; sermons; the application of Canon Law to the debates at the papal court; and the evolution of John Moorman's studies on St Francis and his followers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aFranciscans, Mendicants, England, John Moorman.1 aCanning, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCusato, Michael F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunstan, Petà, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawrence, C.H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanti, Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobson, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoest, Bert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöhrkasten, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteer, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZut